	tion Required: Registration is not required.\n\nDetailed Description: This
	 service is free and available to individuals only. The free service is no
	t available for business tax returns. To receive tax help\, bring the foll
	owing documents:\,\n\nRequired:\n\nPhoto identification\, Social Security 
	cards or Individual Taxpayer Identification Numbers \\(ITIN\\) for everyon
	e listed on the tax return.\, Proof of income\, for example\, W2s and 1099
	s \\(Social Security benefits\\)\, Official documents on Social Security A
	dministration letterhead\, Medicare card \\(if Social Security number is f
	ollowed by an "A"\\)\, Be prepared to provide information about health car
	e coverage for each person on the return.\,\n\nRecommended:\n\nLast year&'
	s tax return\, if available\, Bank account and routing numbers for direct 
	deposit of refunds\, Photocopies or computer print-outs of any of these do
	cuments will be accepted.Original documents highly recommended.\, Due to f
	ederal budget cuts the IRS is unable to provide the Library with certain t
	ax forms and instruction booklets.\, Most IRS forms are available online a
	t\n\nwww.irs.gov .\, You may make free black-and-white prints of the forms
	 from Library computers:\n\nwww.spl.org/Print \, Thanks to our partner\n\n
	AARP .\n\nEvent Logistics: AARP Tax Help locations serve anyone who earned
	 less than $80\,000 in 2025.\, For eligibility details\, contact AARP at 8
	88-227-7669.\n\nContact Us: If you have questions about this event\,\n\nAs
